<normalised orig="justifie" auto="true">justify</normalised> them, and take them to his glory. If you suppose us in all <lb/>
this to have Pleaded our own cause; We hope we are not such as <lb/>
are <normalised orig="intollerable" auto="true">intolerable</normalised> in the Ministry or communion of the Church: If <lb/>
you suppose us to Plead the cause of others, we hope you will accept <lb/>
our desires as impartial, when it is supposed the persons differ <lb/>
from us, as well as from you. We have now faithfully, and not <lb/>
